But Morrison told the court: 'I wasn't burying my head in the sand. It was confusion.' 

The bench adjourned the trial until Wednesday, September 2, and warned him that the case may proceed in his absence should he not turn up.

Morrison was released on bail on the condition that he does not contact prosecution witnesses or go to the family's home again.

 

